A car crashed into Glasgow Airport, engulfing the terminal in flames.
Witnesses described a 4X4 rammed into the building, sparking fears of a terrorist attack.
British Prime Minister Gordon Brown confirmed it was an intentional assault, prompting a critical security threat level.
The incident followed a foiled car bomb plot in London, leading to heightened security measures at airports nationwide.
Two suspects were arrested in connection with the attacks.
The burning vehicle at Glasgow Airport was linked to the London incidents, emphasizing the need for vigilance and support for law enforcement.
